dismissalText.commentary: Chamu Chibhabha c †Sarfaraz Ahmed b Shoaib Malik 99 (100b 11x4 1x6 153m) SR: 99

dismissalComment.html: Strangled down leg for 99. Given out.. He shakes his head before looking skywards. This was an innocuous ball drifting down leg, Chibhabha seeks to help it away with a sweep but does not get hold of it. I think he did not touch the ball even as Sarfraz hung onto a sharp catch, moving to his left. Chibhabha has to wait for his maiden century

And he comes into business. The umpire's forefinger goes up but Masakadza shakes his head as he walks back. This was flighted on off stump, he sinks down to one knee but does not connect with the attempted reverse sweep. Not sure if the ball had popped off the forearm or the glove. Hafeez dives forward to take a low catch. Masakadza has to drag himself off the field..
Chips a soft return catch. Tossed up invitingly on middle. Williamson strides forward, aims to drive, instead he lobs it back to the bowler, who snaps it up near chest-height

dismissalComment.html: Coventry nicks off now. Mighty full, near yorker outside off. Coventry makes room but can't swing it away. He only manages an outer edge that is swallowed by Sarfraz

the sub fielder takes it. The umpires check for a possible no ball. Creamer has been asked to wait. It is a legal ball and Creamer has to depart. Change in pace. Full on off, he wants to hoist it over cover but does not connect well. Skewed off the toe end of the bat to Shehzad

dismissalText.commentary: Azhar Ali c Williams b Mupariwa 102 (104b 8x4 0x6 171m) SR: 98.07

dismissalComment.html: he has! With a short ball that's beem smashed straight to point. Nothing particularly threatening about the ball, should really have done a lot better with that. But after scoring 102, perhaps some tiredness crept in. We can give him some slack. Good innings, set up the chase very well.

dismissalText.commentary: Haris Sohail not out 52 (49b 6x4 0x6 81m) SR: 106.12

dismissalComment.html: excellent work on the long-off boundary. But this was as much the bowler's trick. Looped the ball up over Hafeez's eyeline, made him play just enough away from his body to ensure his timing wouldn't be as good and the chip carries only as far as Coventry - who runs to his left and slides to take a smart, low catch

headshotImage.longCaption: Asad Shafiq player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: excellent work, and Zimbabwe are back in it. Runs down the track and hopes to exploit the vacant midwicket region, but Cremer is getting the ball to dip and turn. Very risky option, and the leading edge results. Raza at short cover runs in, dives and plucks a good one

plumb and the forefinger goes up. Chibhabha strikes in his first over after being becoming the first Zimbabwe player to be out on 99. Sarfraz, who was standing outside the crease, shuffles across and misses the sweep to a full, straight ball in front of middle. Smacked on the back pad

commentTextItems.html: a delicate little dab to third man finishes it off. That's Pakistan's third successful chase of 250-plus in four years. They also wrap up the series 2-0

commentPostTextItems.html: That's all we have for you. Thanks for your company and your comments for enlivening the game. Pakistan have taken the ODIs 2-0, with one more to play. Hope you'll be with us then as well

Azhar Ali is the Man of the Match "Good performance from the team. Obviously you want to perform as captain. It's been fabulous in both the series. All the seniors have helped guide me, they have taught me to concentrate on my game and focus on the controllables. Working on my batting, modern cricket has become fast and you need to keep pace with it and I hope with the grace of God, I can. Great effort from the boys, bowling was very good on a batting wicket to keep them to 268. Everyone knows we have a long way to go, but everyone is giving an effort. Thanks to the crowd as well"
Taqi Muhammad: "Has anybody noticed that Azhar Ali strike rate in all but one ODI since he became Captain has been 90+?"

"Guys tried really hard. Raz and Chamu played really well. Lots of effort out there. Thought it was a drier wicket, still 20-30 short," says Hamilton Masakadza, "Don't get to play that many games, so the guys have to rally and pull something out the hat."

11.50 pm The two Pakistan batsman walk off with broad smiles. Zimbabwe might wonder what they could have done better. Admittedly, with the bowlers they had and the score to which they were limited to, this might well be as far as they could have gotten. Only legspinner Greame Cremer posed enough threat. Their medium pacers were blunted on a healthy batting track. Indeed, Azhar Ali's wicket, after a well-controlled 102, looked to come off a tired shot than something of the bowler's doing. Then Shoaib Malik and Haris Sohail finished it off without much fuss
Arslaan: "hearing the crowd chanting 'ZIM-BAB-WE!!' Is actually really heart warming. Appreciation being shown to the visitors for bringing international cricket back to Pakistan :D "

commentTextItems.html: lovely drive through cover. That's his fifty. It's that lift over the off side that he looks so good playing. Gets down the track, and beside the ball to have all the room he needs to reach the boundary
full and angled in on leg stump, Haris goes for a slog. Appears like he's got an inside edge onto pad and then down to third man

headshotImage.caption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Brian Vitori player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Brian Vitori player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: lots of width and Malik scythes it over cover. There is protection there though
inside edge onto pad as he looks to flick a good length ball off his pads and away to square leg. Ends up settling for a single to point
fuller ball on middle, Malik moves away beside the ball this time and crashes it through cover. That's fifty for this pair off only 37 balls. Terrific little cameo here from the comeback man
in the slot and Malik pastes it away to the long-off boundary. Help yourself medium pace is further impaired by a featherbed of a track
full on middle, almost a yorker, drilled down the ground to long-on

headshotImage.caption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: good length ball on off stump, blocked

commentPreTextItems.html: Xeidy: "That century has done wonders for Malik's confidence..He is batting with authority which has been seen missing ever since his slump started and that was the reason he could not deliver at international stage despite showing great form in domestic circuit. I love watching Shoaib play like this. Credit to management for sending him early in his last ODI so he could take time on pitch and rebuild that lost confidence. He has so much experience. Just needed that one inning to bring all that swagger back. His experience is going to be valuable now that Afridi and Misbah are gone."

commentTextItems.html: outside edge bisects third man running in from the boundary and point running back. Haris races down the track, gets a bouncer for his troubles. Reaches for it with a slash and survies
fuller delivery outside off, slapped away over cover

commentPreTextItems.html: Adnan: "Have'nt Boundary ropes been moved in alot? " ---- Yep, but there is a minimum limit set by the ICC. It's just Lahore is a huge ground

commentTextItems.html: back of a length and on off stump, slid to point

commentPreTextItems.html: Twenty-three off five overs. Appears simple enough

commentTextItems.html: banged in short, Malik swivels on his back foot and pulls to long leg
slower ball in response to the batsman skipping down the track, caressed through the covers

headshotImage.caption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentPreTextItems.html: Ahsan Butt: "BOOM BOOM has arrived, in NatWest t20 Blast though. "

commentTextItems.html: good length ball on middle and leg, tapped to long-on
clean! It was overpitched outside off and Malik got under it and powered it over extra cover. Stunning hit, first one of the innings
seems he hasn't shied away from the late cut yet. Watches the ball quite carefully and slices it away quite fine amid the crowd chanting "Zim-bab-we"

commentPreTextItems.html: Thirty-six off the final six overs
Mukesh: "I guess George Bailey has the record being the captain in his very first international match. It was a T20 though."

commentTextItems.html: good length outside off, Malik drags it to deep midwicket
